    ID: "1003",
    Title: "How to public speak",
    Content:
      '<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><div style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><iframe allowfullscreen="" data-thumbnail-src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EAL1Nd3A0Xo/0.jpg" frameborder="0" height="266" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EAL1Nd3A0Xo?feature=player_embedded" style="clear: right; float: right;" width="320"></iframe><span lang="EN-US">1.<span style="font-size: 7pt; font-stretch: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir="LTR"></span><b><span lang="EN-US">Prepare.</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> No secret. Your thoughts, ideas should be organized, structured, you need to have a message in mind that you want to put across and an objective to attain.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><span lang="EN-US"><br /></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">2.<span style="font-size: 7pt; font-stretch: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir="LTR"></span><b><span lang="EN-US">Practice.</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> I like rehearsing and practing. Put yourself in front of camera or record your voice. Practice. Communication skills are natural for some but not for the rest of us. You need to give it sufficient time to get better at it.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><span lang="EN-US"><br /></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">3.<span style="font-size: 7pt; font-stretch: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir="LTR"></span><b><span lang="EN-US">Watch and learn from others.</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> Whether it is videos or audio, listen to how people handle conversations, how they respond, how they manage tough questions etc. By oberserving and listening, you learn a lot and you might also model.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><span lang="EN-US"><br /></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">4.<span style="font-size: 7pt; font-stretch: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir="LTR"></span><b><span lang="EN-US">Learn from your mistakes.</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> Learn to self-evaluate to improve and not to stop and say you’re bad at public speaking. Be aware and present when you speak. Make notes and work on your weaknesses.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><span lang="EN-US"><br /></span></div><br /><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">5.<span style="font-size: 7pt; font-stretch: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir="LTR"></span><b><span lang="EN-US">Read and listen to audio books.</span></b><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp; You need to be exposed to language in all its forms. By reading and listening you expand your vocabulary, idioms, figures of speech and that way you get more comfortable and have a language baggage you can use when at need.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><span lang="EN-US"><br /></span></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">Let\'s stay in touch and please like, comment and share the video if you liked it.</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/safaanhairy/</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">Twitter: https://twitter.com/safaanhairy</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">Instagram: http://instagram.com/safaanhairy</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">My blog: http://safaanhairy.blogspot.com/</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;">Website: http://www.imediart.ma</div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><br /><br /><br /></div><div style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; text-indent: -.25in;"><br /></div></div>',
    Excerpt: "",
