    ID: "1039",
    Title: "Flourless Pizza: Soooo gooooood!!!!",
    Content:
      '<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;">If you\'re looking for new recipes to eat healthy, this one if you.<br /><br /><div style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-aJnVQbd8CXg/VLfkcG_x5LI/AAAAAAAAULw/gm2am2CO-Gk/s1600/pizza.jpg" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-aJnVQbd8CXg/VLfkcG_x5LI/AAAAAAAAULw/gm2am2CO-Gk/s1600/pizza.jpg" height="240" width="320" /></a></div>Ditch flour and opt for cauliflower for your pizza crust. A lot of videos on Youtube show different ways of making the flourless pizza. The way I make it is I steam cauliflower for about 15min. I then smush it with a fork, add an egg, salt and pepper and mix everything. The dough is ready. Lay it on a plate and put it in the oven for about 15-20min.<br /><br />Take it out the crust from the oven. Now you add whatever you like: tomato sauce, mushroom, tuna, pepper, cheese etc. And put it back in the oven until ready.<br /><br />Enjoy it and let me know what you think ;)<br /><br /><br /></div>',
